items.name: India Reynolds
items.description:
A request of @Bzas76. Sorry I couldn't work with an older dataset, mate, but I hope you'll like this one!

India Reynolds is a British model and social media celebrity, known for her recent stint in Love Island, among other things.

Update: Retrained from scratch, since my work process has changed quite a bit since I did this TI. I think the previous version, even if it was only a 200-step one, was very good, but perhaps slightly less accurate than desired. India looked gorgeous in almost every pic, though, which is why I was hesitant to update the model. I think this new version (2.0) captures her looks better without losing terrain in terms of beauty.

This new version is a 1000 step TI, trained on a dataset of 18 images.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (1nd1areyn0lds:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, turtleneck sweater, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6".

items.name: PharaohX
items.description:
Creates Realistic Egyptian Pharaohs and Egyptian Pharaoh based concepts. Tested with and works best on Chilloutmix model. 15 handpicked images were used from various sources to create this model.

Other Relevant Information:

  • Best weight is 0.45-0.7 ideally, I use 0.4-0.6. However, as always you can try different weights as per your will.

  • Trigger word is phr8

  • This is a good NEGATIVE prompt for the chilloutmix model in general

  • Works well with Controlnet OpenPose (samples with throne hands pose and bent posture is made with openpose)

  • EasyNegative, paintings, sketches, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, normal quality, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), skin spots, acnes, skin blemishes, age spot, glans,extra fingers,fewer fingers,strange fingers,bad hand,backlight, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark, logo, bad anatomy, nude, topless, fat,EasyNegative

  • Start with this prompt followed by your actual prompt (realistic, photo-realistic:1.37), (8k, RAW photo, best quality, masterpiece:1.2), photorealistic, best quality, extremely detailed face, extremely detailed eyes and face

  • If the LORA is too strong, insert the LORA somewhere along the end/middle of the prompt with lowered weights. Also change CFG accordingly. Heun is a good sampler.

  • Looking forward to reviews/criticisms. I encourage users to share criticisms as a comment rather than a lower star review, so that I or community members can try to help out with your problems.

Finally, I would really appreciate if you respect the terms I have released it under, thanks!

items.name: Zelrik's character's style - Female version
items.description:
This is the first version of my female LORA model. It includes quite a bit of my own style.

For future version, follow me on Instagram/Join my patreon, I'll give early access to future versions to patreon members (starting at the intermediate tier):

  • https://www.instagram.com/the_real_zoi.ai/

  • https://www.patreon.com/the_real_zoi_ai

What's in it:

  • Several handpicked style elements to bias your characters in certain moods/clothing styles

  • Does well with wings/biomech and eye styling. You'll often get some glowing 'red' eyes if you prompt for it (and even if you don't).

  • Trained on decently realistic images but also capable of handling anime style

  • This is a very busty character by design with a heavy bias in favor of cleavage-showing outfits, it will show more or less depending on prompt and base model.

  • There is no porn in the training data so it will handle nsfw depending on the base model you use.

  • Trigger word is generally 'Zelrik woman'

Testing extensively on:

  • Hassan model 1.5

  • Lunar Diffusion model (see https://www.patreon.com/mooncryptowow for details)

Currently also testing on:

  • Uberreal

  • Protogen

Cons:

This is the first version and has its bugs/issues.

  • Some prompts trigger some annoying glow/glare that you'll have to deal with.

  • There are some anatomy artifacts also that I am working on reducing.

  • If your renders look 'overcook'/wrong. Reduce the Lora weight and play with the cfg scale and other parameters, it does not behave the same depending on the base model you use.

Sample Images:

Sample images are txt2img with upscaling, a few of them have minor photoshop touchups but not all of them.

Disclaimer:

  • Not for commercial use by default. If you need it for commercial use, contact me first.

  • I spent a lot of time tweaking that style, please credit me if you post images online.

  • You can probably make a lot of nsfw content with it, use it responsibly.

items.name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball - All Series) LoRA
items.description:
Son Goku LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

If you want a Goku LoRA that's also using the style from the anime, please check out @Kizaru 's Son Goku - Dragon Ball Z / Super (LoRA).

I made this LoRA because I needed a version of Goku that wasn't bound to a specific artstyle so that I could use it with my Akira Toriyama Style LoRA and with NED.

This one should be flexible enough in reproducing most Goku's forms, including SSj4. SSj3 is the hardest but still manages with higher weight. What I like is that you can also make a realistic Goku with it.

Please use son goku in the prompts for better accuracy (but should also work without it, just less accurate), as well as descriptive tags. This should be flexible enough to allow any outfit and hairstyle, while still allowing you to make Goku. Weight should be around 1.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Kiryuin Satsuki (Kill La Kill) LoRA
items.description:
This is a LoRA to generate Kiryuin Satsuki from Kill La Kill.

  • I suggest using this LoRA at 0.7-1.0 weight for best results.

  • These images were generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, Corneo's 7th Heaven Mix, My Own Mix with the OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE. (I'm lazy.)

  • Always add this to the prompt to activate it - kiryuin satsuki

  • She can be placed in any clothes but if you wish to put her in traditional clothes: junketsu, epaulettes, school uniform, skirt, white thigh boots

  • If you wish to place her in Junketsu: junketsu, revealing clothes, clothing cutout, cleavage cutout, white panties, white thighhighs

  • It can do portraits, upper body and cowboy shot pretty well at 512x512

  • I suggest generating at 768x768 for higher quality pictures. It's also suggested using this resolution for full body.

  • You can add weapon, sword to prompt if you want to generate her sword - It doesn't always come out good.

All pictures were upscaled using these settings:

  • Upscaler: Fatal-Anime 4x

  • Hires. Steps: 25

  • Denoising Strength: 0.5

  • Upscale by 1.5

Known Issues

  • It struggles with full body @ 512x512 but you can fix this but either upscaling or just generated at 768x768.

  • Sometimes when you're putting her in other clothes that aren't her school uniform or Junketsu - It will make her collar regardless. You can stop this by adding Detached Collar in negative prompt.

  • Sometimes It will generate very faded blue eyes that It looks grey - This is because of like three pictures in the dataset, I believe.

Embeds and LoRAs used

Bad Prompt - Ekune Style LoRA

Follow me on Twitter for updates- https://twitter.com/TrueHeroBang

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune

V2 description

Prompting for V2 works the same as for V1 so refer to description below. Preview images were made with weight 0.9.

Sadly V2 still share the same shortcoming as V1, that being command spells. Not only they don't work as intended, but tbh I feel like they drag the whole image quality down.

That said, if you're not going to use them then V2 produces more consistent and better outputs in most of cases :) keep in mind that you can add muscular to negatives if you feel like he's looking too buff, which seems to happen more often than before.

Lora model for Kotomine Kirei. I wanted to do it for the memes, but the model ended up pretty cool (although I still have problem with training many words at once). For me it worked best at weight 0.7.

The main tag used is kotomine kirei. To get the FSN outfit add to that cross necklace, black pants, black shirt, purple coat. Fate Zero outfit is similiar cross necklace, black pants, black shirt, long sleeves. You can also change long sleeves to short sleeves if you feel like whooping Shirou's ass.

Hairstyle depends on where you put parted bangs tag. In normal prompt you get the FSN look, in negative prompt you get the Fate Zero look.

I also tried training tags control spell arm and control spell hand, but they don't work so well. The good thing is that when they appear they look fine.

And also I tried to train black keys which you have best chance to get if you use black keys, holding weapon, dual wielding, between fingers. But they don't really look anything like they suppose to.

More useful tags: muscular - extra ripped, stole - priest scarf thingie.

20世纪初叶，在上海形成并开始广泛流传的通俗图画读物始称连环画，俗称“小人书”。中华人民共和国成立后，连环画作为一种通俗的传播文化的艺术形式得到迅速发展，形成中国现代美术的一个主要画种。谨以此LOAR模型纪念这种离我们越来越远的艺术风格。

（但有些模型会有一种非常令人脑洞大开的艺术效果，出乎意料，XD）

In the early 20th century, popular pictorial books formed in Shanghai and began to circulate widely were called comic books, commonly known as "Little People's Books". After the founding of the People's Republic of China, comic books developed rapidly as a popular art form for spreading culture, forming one of the main types of modern Chinese art.
This LOAR model commemorates this art style that is getting farther and farther away from us.
(But some models will have a very mind-blowing artistic effect, unexpectedly, XD)

items.name: Ferrari F40
items.description:
This is my model for the Ferrari F40, one of my all time favorite cars! The model was trained on very very high resolution images, so this should work well for images above 768x768.

A few things about the model: The trigger word is FerFourty, using this will trigger the Lora. Second, all of the images were trained on red Ferrari F40's but it's still easy to make different color cars, just note what color you want it to be, and in the negative prompt section include "red car" this will basically guarantee the car turns out the color you want. Third, like with most car models, if the resolution becomes something non-square, sometimes it will want to include multiple cars, so you can also negative prompt "multiple cars" and "2cars" to help increase the odds of just having a single normal car.

Other than that, you can keep the weight wherever you see fit. I typically like it at 0.8, but depending on your base checkpoint, it might be different. POST YOUR PICS! I want to see the model used with different art styles! With your permission, I might include it in the showcase for the model!

items.name: EndlessMix
items.description:
EndlessMix is a merge of multiple models

For sampling methods, use either Euler a or DPM++ 2M Karras

DOWNLOAD/INSTALLATION

Step 1: download SAFETENSORS file.

Step 2: put the SAFETENSORS file under "stable-diffusion-webui\models\Stable-diffusion"

Step 3: Done! enjoy the model

USAGE

-use a minimal negative prompt for best results

-use Euler A or DPM++ 2M Karras and 20-25 steps for best results

-use danbooru tags

-I used a CLIP blending (optional) Link to script: https://gist.github.com/catboxanon/bdcf23a2699c920da0d8177dbfa34e15

https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/discussions/8266

-I use the upscaler Latent (nearest) with a highres step of 0-20 and denoise of 0.6 for when there's a detailed background (optional)

-I use the upscaler Latent (nearest-exact) with a highres step of 0-20 and denoise of 0.6 for close up of characters (optional)

EXAMPLE PROMPT

masterpiece, best quality, ultra-detailed, beautiful lighting, 1girl, short hair, (multicolored hair:1.2), green eyes, cowboy shot, turtleneck, turtleneck sweater


negative prompt: (low quality, worst quality:1.4)

VAE

No VAE is needed, loras should work as intended. Using a VAE could make your images look "burnt" or "fried".

CREDIT TO THE PEOPLE WHO MADE THE MODELS Ether Blu Mix, AnyHentai and iCoMix
